Choose a small size frying pan.
Put the frying pan on the oven.
Turn on the oven and preheat the frying pan for 1 minute so it's warm enough.
Add some oil or butter to the pan and allow it to be heated for another minute on moderate gas.
Add some salt to the oil and turn it around the pan for a few seconds.
Break the egg right in middle of the pan and wait for 3 minutes to fry your egg.
Add some salt to the top of the frying egg as well as some peper.
Base on your preference, wait for as long as the white becomes as crispy as you want.
Turn the whole frying egg to the other side so the folk is also heated for no more than 5 seconds.
Turn off the oven.
Pick your favorite plate, serve your frying egg on your plate and design it with vegetables and the likes.
Your Crispy fried egg with its juicy yolk is ready to be eaten, Bon Appetite! 
